main event: Two whitish objects were observed crossing the sky in Coudersport, Pennsylvania on June 19, 1960.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 20 minutes,The objects changed directions before disappearing over the horizon,They were first observed moving toward the East and disappeared to the West,One witness described a whirring sound associated with the objects,The witness stated that similar sightings had been reported regularly from East Coudersport.
witness description: The witness was looking at the sky from a car window and had prior experience with unusual aerial phenomena.
